The Herald Crime Reporter Jaison Muvevi (43), who is facing a plethora of offences including killing three people in Hwedza has been linked to a fourth murder case. The case is alleged to have occurred in Harare where Muvevi is alleged to have killed a woman in unclear circumstances in the Avenues area, Harare. National police spokesperson Assistant Commissioner Paul Nyathi confirmed saying Muvevi is also facing a third attempted murder case. Muvevi was facing three counts of murder and two for attempted murder.